'''Per Øystein Grimstad''' (born 7 January 1934) is a Norwegian businessperson, diplomat and politician for the [[Norwegian Labour Party|Labour Party]].

He was born in [[Sandnessjøen]], and is a [[sivilingeniør|siv.ing.]] by education. He was the CEO of [[Norconsult]] from 1980 to 1986, a [[State Secretary (Norway)|State Secretary]] in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Industry|Ministry of Industry]] from 1986 to 1988, director of the [[Norwegian Agency for Development Cooperation]] from 1988 to 1996 and the Norwegian ambassador to [[South Africa]] from 1996 to 2000.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Per Ø. Grimstad|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Per_%C3%98._Grimstad|language=Norwegian|accessdate=5 March 2009}}</ref>

He used to be married to the singer [[Birgitte Grimstad]].<ref name=snl/>

